{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 3.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds1|text', 'text' : 'O come, all you nations. Know the power of the awe-inspiring mystery. For Christ our Savior, the Logos who was in the beginning, voluntarily for us was crucified and buried, and He rose from the dead to save the universe. Let us worship Him.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 3.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds2|text', 'text' : 'Those who guarded You reported all the marvelous events, O Lord. However the Sanhedrin of futility filled their hands with gifts, thinking that in this way they could hide Your resurrection, which the world glorifies. Have mercy on us.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 3.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds3|text', 'text' : 'The universe was filled with joy in the experience of Your resurrection. Mary Magdalene came unto the tomb and found an Angel sitting upon the stone. With his garments flashing like lightning, he said to her, "Why do you seek among the dead the One who is alive? He is not here, but has risen as He said, and is going before you to Galilee."'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds4|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 3.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds4|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|Lauds4|text', 'text' : 'In Your light we will see light, O Master who loves humanity; for You have risen from the dead, and You granted salvation to the human race, so that all creation may glorify You, only sinless One. Have mercy on us.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|peMA|MM|Lauds1234|text', 'text' : 'For media only.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|alt1|peCommemoration|text', 'text' : 'Bright Tuesday. Memory of the holy, glorious, lately-appearing, and miracle-working monastic Martyrs, Raphael and Nicholas, and the holy Virgin Martyr Irene, who were in Thermi on the Island of Lesbos'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|alt1|peShortCommemoration1|text', 'text' : 'Bright Tuesday. Memory of Sts. Raphael, Nicholas and Irene.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|alt1|peCom1|title', 'text' : 'For Sts. Raphael, Nicholas and Irene.'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|alt1|peInsert1', 'text' : 'the holy, glorious, lately-appearing, and miracle-working monastic Martyrs Raphael, Nicholas, and Irene,'}
{'id_' : 'pe|d073_en_US_dedes|alt1|peInsert2', 'text' : 'whose memory we celebrate,'}
